caption: Loved the big portion sized meals, small wait time in between delivery but still so worth it. You'll be content with whatever you get.
Excellent family owned restaurant with an extensive menu for a very fair price. Had a roasted duck soup, full of flavors and perfect cooking execution.

The lady that helped us was so nice and the food was delicious. What more do you need? They also have great prices! I'm vegetarian and my noodles were just what I wanted. My husband had the roasted duck with rice noodles and he loved his dish. We will be back.

This is my go to spot for authentic Chinese cuisine. They have a pretty large menu and everything I have tried has been excellent. Their roast duck is delicious, anything they have over rice or noodles is a great choice,  their noodle soups are full of flavor and my favorite thing to get. They currently had a $1 increase in price on all items but they are still very affordable and they deliver with Grubhub. The owner and his family are very friendly and polite. I have no complaints at all. I will be eating here as long as this place stays open.
Awesome experience, food was delicious, when I walked in they were super nice to me and overall amazing experience, will definitely go back
The beef soup is fantastic.
The best wonton and noodle based soups in Chicago. Reminds me of West Coast style.

Even before the boy and I started dating, he was always raving about Harris- but for some odd reason, we never ended up here until a few years later.  We recently went, and I can say that it was rather delightful experience.
Excellent Food, Quick Service
Usually, I don't write reviews but this place was super nice!! Lovely family-owned restaurant and the best beef noodle soup I ever had, thank you!
Great place and foods are really delicious.

one of the tastiest places in Chinatown. I love their broth of their noodle soups, beef brisket noodle soup is a classic. I also came for other basic Chinese dishes and it was delicious. The only bad thing is that it's far into Chinatown and most people would of went into other restaurants before making it this far in. I can see this place popping with business if it was in a better location.

For sure we were ordering their famous dried fried chicken wings & some fried rice as well. My friend was hungry though, so we asked our waitress what was the second best thing & she said everything else that isn't the dry wings LOL so we got the lemon chicken.
Service was great,  recommendations were excellent.
Great flavor and all around good food
This restaurant has sat in my collections for a LONG TIME. And this past weekend, I had the opportunity to try it. Oh boy is it good. It's really good.

I have tried so many times to get a seat here and I finally did on a Friday afternoon! There was no wait and I was able to immediately order the famous fried chicken. The lunch special was still an option so the six pieces I ordered also came with soup. I also ordered 6 pan fried dumplings.
Very Nice staff, quick service, good food and big portions for relatively low cost
Great food and great service!
Big portions. Best deal in Chinatown that I know of.

Portions are generous especially for the price. Cozy local place has that "hidden gem" feel. Egg drop soup was thick and the pot stickers are about the size of a tennis ball. You will not leave this place hungry or unhappy.

This place is amazing, great prices, friendly and fast service and the food tastes awesome. My Chinese friends recommended this place to me and it seems the flavor is pretty similar to authentic food in Cantonese cuisine. Will go back for sure.
Great food and chinese ambiance.

Right when we sat down, we immediately ordered. We ordered sautéed green beans, chicken fried rice, two orders of dry fried chicken and black bean sauce noodles. This was shared amongst 4 people. We finished majority of the food. As always we were  satisfied and cannot wait to come back for the dry fried chicken ! Yummy Yummy Noodles
I mean...come on lol look at the price and the amount of food that they serve👀 also tastyyyyy
Great noodles!
Good food. Good prices. Can't complain.
Sliced beef wonton soup spicy, wow amazing!  Melt in your mouth beef, perfect soup.

This is our go to place for chinese take out in Chinatown because they deliver. Their portions are large, quality consistent, and good variety. We try to get different things each time, but I do have my favorites. For the average Chinese take out, this place is not bad. We will mostly likely continue to come because it’s close to our home
"Your order will be ready in 15 minutes"....... half an hour later, "it's almost ready". Why don't you just tell me it will be ready in 45 minutes???

We went to Chinatown for the first time grab some noodles and chicken. We ordered a schezwan dry chicken and chicken ho fun (chicken noodles). Both of the dishes were so bland and only looked good. Either the cook didn't add salt or no garlic nor ginger.babsolutely NO Flavor! Highly disappointed because I really thought it would taste good because it looked good! The lady on the counter was really nice!

I am here in Chicago for a conference and ordered sezhuan chicken. But when I got my delivery....they forgot the sauce! I'm eating popcorn chicken pretty much. I can't even eat this because it's so dry. Keep in mind I never complain about my food. Even when I go to a restaurant. I never ask for a refund or to see a manager. But when you forget the most important part?! It's like me ordering a hamburger but not getting the actual Patty. You can't be serious. I'd give you guys no stars if possible.
Excellent.  Wonderful family run restaurant, great food, large portions, fair prices!
Great prices great Chinatown experience

caption: Really enjoyed the atmosphere of a small family run business.  Food was amazing
(Translated by Google) Perfect place! Huge portions, low prices and very, very tasty!  (Original) Отличное место! Огромные порции, низкие цены и очень, очень вкусно!
The staff were friendly and I had excellent roast duck and noodle soup for lunch, only $8!

Very consistent in quality and taste. If you looking for Chinese comfort food with low price, this is the place. Don’t expect fancy dine-in decor.  Owner always appreciative of your visit. I enjoy their stir fried beef noodles, fried fish balls and egg rolls. yes basic dishes but good.
Hidden gem. The best Cantonese bbq pork i have had in North America.

After coming back from a trip to HK a month ago, I'd been missing some good ole Cantonese food.  So when I was out in Chicago for business, I decided to visit Chinatown to see what I could find. And damn am I glad I found this place.  All the other reviews about value and portion sizes are true. This food is stupid cheap, seriously.  The family that runs the place is extremely friendly and polite - really felt at home here. If this restaurant was in DC, I'd go every week!  Food wise, this is traditional Cantonese fare, not your typical Chinese American restaurant. So the seasoning is more toned down, but honestly, this is home cooking in my book.  There's more than deep dish pizza that brings me to this city

Just went to Yummy Yummy noodles and it is very good value for the quality of food. Good size servings. Very nice service. Not much for Ambience but at least reasonably clean for Chinatown. The orange chicken and the fried Japanese tofu were excellent. The pork spare ribs over rice we're also very good . Unfortunately the shrimp in egg sauce and the beef and egg sauce wild up slightly overdone which made it scrambled eggs instead of an egg sauce, but it was still very tasty. We were a little nervous to eat here since there was no one there when we showed up but glad we gave it a try.
Really tasty home cooked Chinese food. Entrees are on the cheaper side
Good cheap food!

Excellent noodle soups!

I had the Ong choy and beef brisket pork wonton noodle soup. The beer brisket was a little tough. But everything else was really good. Service was excellent and the food was really cheap ($7 noodle soup)!
This was such a treat for our family visiting Chicago on spring break. We really appreciated the friendly service and all of the yummy food. It was a great way to end the day.
Spicy beef shank noodles were delicious! Service was friendly and fast.
This is by far the best noodle place in Chicago!!!
Great food good flavor  not expensive at all love it

Choufun noodle was good. The fried rice had some smoky smell to it as if burnt. Not terrible but odd. Other dishes were ok, but with so many other restaurants in Chinatown offering better food, I don't really see the point of returning to this place.
Delicious noodles for a great price.
Delicious food! Very friendly customer service. Nice little family owned restaurant. Big portions for a low price! Should definitely stop by and eat the food! #TrueReview

Delicious! If you are visiting Chicago's Chinatown I highly recommend eating at Yummy Yummy Noodles. Everything we ordered was amazing and was a great portion for the price. I recommend any of the fried rice options and the fish ball soup!
Loved it

This place keeps me coming back after 5 years amazing soups and spicy cold beef.
Great family operated restaurant, love the food. Service is friendly and informative.
The best veggie noodle soup and beef chow mein ever! 🎉🎉

Yummy food at such a low price! Can’t beat it! You get your choice of noodle type. We tried the spicy beef noodle soup and the pork fried rice. The beef was so tender and melted in your mouth!
Deserves their rating for friendliness, value and taste. Family-run, honest pricing, honest service. English, Mandarin or Cantonese.

Right in China Town.  Don't know why it's so slow on Friday night.  The food was delicious,  the price is hard to believe how low it is.  $5.00 to $6.00 for a good size Noodle bowl.  If you are a traveler and try to meet your budget, this place will fill you up for a small price.
Nice hot food

They are very nice small place but the service was good. Food was delicious best Chinese food so far and I've been to plenty the orange chicken and Singapore noodle I where some of the dishes I had it was tasty we also order the Mongolian beef shrimp fried rice and other dishes from this place and everything was delicious and so fresh I would recommend this place for anyone looking for some good Chinese food and that's a decent price

Authentic AF! Super friendly and accommodating. Extensive menu with everything you could possibly think of in English and Chinese(?). Best general Tsao ever! Definitely try the rice noodles with sliced beef and green peppers. SO GOOD! The bean sauce is very delicious. The portion sizes are VERY reasonably priced. $8.50 could feed two, easily!
